<Base
  title="Medical Disclaimer | Sage & Sprout"
  description="Sage & Sprout's medical disclaimer: all content is for general educational purposes only and is not medical advice."
  breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'Medical Disclaimer', href: '/medical-disclaimer/' }]}
>
  <div style="max-width:680px;margin:0 auto;padding:3rem 1.25rem 5rem;">
    <h1 style="font-family:var(--font-family-display);font-size:clamp(1.8rem,4vw,2.4rem);font-weight:700;color:var(--color-ink);margin:0 0 2rem;">Medical Disclaimer</h1>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        <strong>Effective date: June 27, 2026</strong>
      </p>

      <h2>General educational information only</h2>
      <p>
        All content on Sage &amp; Sprout — including calculators, articles, explanations, and
        all other materials — is provided for <strong>general educational and informational purposes only</strong>.
        It is not intended to be, and should not be construed as, medical advice, medical diagnosis,
        a medical opinion, a treatment plan, or a substitute for professional medical care.
      </p>

      <h2>Not a substitute for professional medical care</h2>
      <p>
        The tools and information on this site do not replace the advice, diagnosis, or treatment
        of a licensed healthcare provider — including but not limited to obstetricians, gynecologists,
        certified nurse midwives, pediatricians, family medicine physicians, or fertility specialists.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Always consult your healthcare provider</strong> with any questions you have about your
        pregnancy, your baby's health, fertility, or any other medical matter. Never delay seeking
        professional medical advice or disregard your provider's guidance based on information you
        read on this site.
      </p>

      <h2>No doctor-patient relationship</h2>
      <p>
        Use of Sage &amp; Sprout does not create a doctor-patient relationship between you and
        the site's authors or reviewers. Communications through this site — including contact form
        submissions — do not establish or constitute a healthcare relationship of any kind.
      </p>

      <h2>Estimates, not predictions</h2>
      <p>
        All calculators produce <strong>estimates based on statistical averages and clinical guidelines</strong>.
        Individual outcomes may vary significantly. For example:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>An estimated due date is the midpoint of a statistical distribution — only about 4–5% of babies are born on their EDD.</li>
        <li>An estimated fertile window is based on average cycle physiology and may not reflect your individual cycle.</li>
        <li>Weight-gain targets and growth percentiles represent population norms, not personalized recommendations.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Your healthcare provider is the appropriate source for personalized guidance that accounts
        for your full medical history and individual circumstances.
      </p>

      <h2>Emergency situations</h2>
      <p>
        If you believe you are experiencing a medical emergency — including but not limited to
        pregnancy complications, preterm labor, heavy bleeding, severe pain, or any situation you
        consider urgent — <strong>call 911 or go to the nearest emergency room immediately.</strong>
        Do not rely on this website in an emergency.
      </p>

      <h2>Accuracy and updates</h2>
      <p>
        We make every effort to ensure the information on this site is accurate, evidence-based,
        and up-to-date. However, medical knowledge evolves. Guidelines are periodically updated by
        professional societies (ACOG, AAP, ASRM, and others), and our content may not always reflect
        the most current recommendations.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you believe any content on this site contains an error, please <a href="/contact/">contact us</a>
        so we can review and correct it.
      </p>

      <h2>Affiliate and advertising disclosure</h2>
      <p>
        Some pages on this site may contain affiliate links or display advertising. Affiliate links
        are disclosed at the point of use with the label "We may earn a commission."
        Advertising does not influence the clinical accuracy or editorial content of our calculators
        or articles.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
